name: 3-demethoxyubiquinol 3-hydroxylase
classes: Acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen;
reaction: 6-methoxy-3-methyl-2-(all-trans-polyprenyl)-1,4-benzoquinol + a reduced acceptor + O2 = 3-demethylubiquinol + acceptor + H2O [RN:R12067]
comment: The enzyme catalyses the last hydroxylation reaction during the biosynthesis of ubiquinone.
